body:
@htuch : Oh, I should have paid more attention to what you were aiming to do when I was reviewing; I read your code but not so much your comments. I think you are talking about this line:

`slice_(request.SerializeAsString()), buf_(grpc::ByteBuffer(&slice_, 1)),`

So, `SerializationTraits<google::protobuf::Message>::Serialize(request, &buf, &own_buffer_)` should have the same effect even though the template parameter is just the base class of the request (the built-in gRPC one only works on Message anyway though we allow people to define them for their own templated classes). When you say "without templating", can you use no templates whatsoever?
